.TH devin-cloud-drs-sandbox-create 1  "sandbox-create " 
.SH NAME
devin\-cloud\-drs\-sandbox\-create \- Create a sandbox Devin session for testing repo setup
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdevin cloud drs sandbox\-create\fR <\fB\-\-repo\fR> [\fB\-\-prompt\fR] [\fB\-\-secret\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Create a sandbox Devin session for testing repo setup
.PP
Spins up a fresh cloud session attached to the given repository. Use `devin cloud drs run` to execute commands inside the sandbox.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-repo\fR \fI<REPO>\fR
Repository in `owner/repo` format (e.g. `simonw/llm`)
.TP
\fB\-\-prompt\fR \fI<PROMPT>\fR [default: Sandbox session for declarative repo setup testing.]
Initial prompt for the sandbox session
.TP
\fB\-\-secret\fR \fI<KEY=VALUE>\fR
Per\-session secret in `KEY=VALUE` form (repeatable)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
